# Portfolio Project Pages

## Page shell
Every `projects/<slug>/index.html` follows:
`nav` → `project-hero` → `project-body-wrap` → `project-layout` (main + aside) → footer + `main.js`

Stylesheets: `../../css/style.css`, `hero.css`, `sections.css`, local `project.css`.

## Hero
- **Tags:** 4–8 relevant tech/domain tags
- **Title:** clear project name
- **Subtitle:** one sentence — outcome + core technologies
- **Meta:** Company, Role, Year, Type (or Location for internships)
- **Cover:** prefer `.cover-label` text or inline SVG — avoid emoji placeholders

## Main content (flexible middle, fixed ends)
**Required:** Overview (1–2 paragraphs: problem/outcome, then how it was solved)

**Choose 1–2 middle sections by project type:**
- Architecture — systems, platforms, pipelines
- Research Approach / Methodology — R&D or process work
- Key Contributions — internship or focused deliverables
- Ingestion Strategy / Data flow — table when multi-path or trade-offs matter

**Always end with:** Key Achievements (or Key Contributions) + Tech Stack grid

**Sidebar:** Other Projects (always); optional summary card (e.g. Platform Layers, Stack at a glance) with 4–6 labeled rows

## Copy
- Lead with impact, then technical depth
- Bullets: verb + outcome (Deployed, Designed, Delivered, Validated)
- Avoid vague claims without a concrete result
- When renaming a project, sync the card in root `index.html` (title, description, tags)

## Architecture diagrams (when used)
- Single **left-to-right** flow in one `.diagram-placeholder` — not stacked unrelated rows
- **Data plane** = solid arrows: Source → Edge/core → Paths/modules → Processing → Storage → Visualization
- **Ops/monitoring** = dashed branch off main flow (manage or health) — not in the KPI data chain
- **Hub node** (`.diag-hub`): composite box with subtitle + inner chip for embedded logic
- **Workflow card** (`.arch-n8n-card` pattern): bordered container with inner mini-flow for orchestration tools
- **Icon nodes** (`.diag-icon-node`): img or SVG + `.diag-icon-name` + `.diag-icon-sub`
- Diagram icons: 20–24px; `overflow-x: auto` on mobile
- Project-specific node names belong in HTML only — the rule defines patterns, not fixed technologies

## Tech stack
- Real logos via Simple Icons: `https://cdn.simpleicons.org/{slug}/{hex}`
- Text badge (`.tech-icon-text`) when no Simple Icon exists (proprietary hardware, protocols)
- External links: `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- Grid: `.tech-grid`; use `.stack-wide` (4 cols) when 9+ items
- No emoji in `.tech-icon` — migrate legacy pages when editing them

## Typography and contrast (`project.css`)
On `.project-hero` and `.project-body-wrap`:
```css
--text-muted: hsl(240, 10%, 72%);
--text-dim: hsl(240, 8%, 54%);
```
Inside `.diagram-placeholder` only:
```css
--diag-label: hsl(45, 90%, 62%);
```
Use `--diag-label` for diagram subtitles only (`.diag-icon-sub`, `.diag-hub-sub`, `.diag-arrow-label`, etc.). Keep node titles on `--text` / `--white`.

## CSS conventions
- Per-project styles in `projects/<slug>/project.css` — avoid shared `css/` unless site-wide
- Reuse diagram classes: `.arch-flow`, `.arch-col`, `.diag-hub`, `.arch-n8n-card`, `.ingestion-table`, `.sidebar-layer`
- When adding diagram styles to a legacy page, copy the arch block from `projects/opc-ua-transformation/project.css`

